The paper deals with generating image captions using natural language processing techniques and frame semantics, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also involves visual grounding, which is a key aspect of computer vision (cs.CV). The model developed in the paper involves learning and generating captions, which is a task that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves using linguistic data available on the web, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
